"""
TradeSynchronizer — Tradovate APPLICATION credentials.

These are NOT user credentials. They identify TradeSynchronizer
itself as an application to Tradovate's REST API, independently
of which user is logging in. You set them ONCE for the entire
project, regardless of how many Tradovate accounts (personal,
demo, prop-firm sub-accounts like Apex/TopStep/MFFU) you later
authenticate against from inside the app.

One-time setup
──────────────
1. Sign in to Tradovate (any Tradovate account works — a free Demo
   account is fine; you do NOT need an "API plan" or a prop-firm
   account here).
2. Go to https://trader.tradovate.com → click your user icon →
   "API Access".
3. Click "Register an App". Pick any name (e.g. "TradeSynchronizer"),
   any version (e.g. "1.0").
4. Tradovate emits two strings:
        cid   — a numeric-looking string (e.g. "8723")
        sec   — a long alphanumeric secret
5. Copy this template:
        cp tradesync/_app_credentials.py.example  tradesync/_app_credentials.py
   and fill in the two values below.

The real file `tradesync/_app_credentials.py` is .gitignored, so
your secret never ends up in version control.

User credentials (username/password of the Tradovate account you
actually trade on, including prop-firm accounts) still live in the
GUI's Live / Demo tabs — they're per-user, per-environment.
"""

APP_CID = ""   # ← fill in your Tradovate-issued client id
APP_SEC = ""   # ← fill in your Tradovate-issued API secret
